<paragraph id="8BC736F9FFF3FFA4FF6D2ED68BD8FF42" blockId="2.[136,1452,2015,2074]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,159,289]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="78" pageId="2" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis id="B90CEAEBFFF3FFA5FF6D2ED688E9F86E" bold="true" box="[136,243,2015,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="77">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
—The species is morphologically similar to the adjacently distributed 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D7AFFF3FFA5FC742EE98CFAF86D" authority="W. P. Li &amp; Z. Li" authorityName="W. P. Li &amp; Z. Li" box="[913,1248,2016,2038]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="huangpingensis">
<emphasis id="B90CEAEBFFF3FFA5FC742EE98C58F86E" box="[913,1090,2016,2037]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="77">A. huangpingensis</emphasis>
W. P. Li &amp; Z. Li
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE94B08FFF3FFA5FB092EE98DBAF86D" author="Li, Z. &amp; Xiong, Y. C. &amp; Liao, J. J. &amp; Xiao, J. W. &amp; Li, W. P." box="[1260,1440,2016,2038]" pageId="2" pageNumber="77" pagination="235 - 244" refId="ref2278" refString="Li, Z., Xiong, Y. C., Liao, J. J., Xiao, J. W. &amp; Li, W. P. (2020) Aster huangpingensis (Asteraceae, Astereae), a new species from Guizhou, China. Phytotaxa 433 (3): 235 - 244. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 433.3.5" type="journal article" year="2020">
Li 
<emphasis id="B90CEAEBFFF3FFA5FAED2EE98D23F86E" box="[1288,1337,2016,2037]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="77">et al.</emphasis>
2020: 242
</bibRefCitation>
), but mainly differs in the following characters: leaves inconspicuously triplinerved (vs. conspicuously veined), leaf blades ovate to oblong-lanceolate (vs. narrowly oblanceolate or spatulate), involucre cylindric-campanulate (vs. campanulate), peduncle and pedicels glabrous (vs. sparsely strigillose), achenes 4-ribbed (vs. 2- or 3-ribbed).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
